This is the Diamond Light Source Ltd Scientific Software Python package.

To run, make sure the python installation contains NumPy, PIL, pylibtiff, Matplotlib and
SciPy packages.

$ PYTHONPATH=$SCISOFTPATH/src:$PYTHONPATH python

where SCISOFTPATH is the path to the directory this package is located.

>>> import scisoftpy as dnp
>>> help(dnp.io)


Eclipse setup

Pydev > Interpreter - Python
 Libraries
  python site-packages
  numpy site-packages, matplotlib egg
  wxPython site-packages, wx-2.8-gtk2-unicode sub-directory and wx sub-sub
  scipy...
 Environment
  LD_LIBRARY_PATH to wxGTK libraries
